This is a Windows command that launches the Island browser with specific flags:

- "C:\Program Files\Island\Island\Application\Island.exe" — The Island browser executable (standard Windows install path)

- --origin-trial-disabled-features=CanvasTextNg|WebAssemblyCustomDescriptors — Disables two specific Chromium origin trial features:
  - CanvasTextNg — A newer canvas text rendering implementation
  - WebAssemblyCustomDescriptors — A WebAssembly proposal for custom property descriptors
  
  Origin trials are experimental web platform features that sites can opt into. This flag prevents these specific trials from activating, likely to avoid compatibility issues or known bugs.

- --restart — Tells the browser to restart (typically used when the browser is relaunching itself, e.g., after an update or a crash recovery).

In short: It's restarting the Island browser with two experimental web features explicitly disabled. This is likely an auto-generated command from the browser's own update/restart mechanism, not something a user would type manually.
